<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07947</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT TO PROVIDE FOR A STUDY AND FOR DEMONSTRATION PROJECTS REGARDING CASES OF HEPATITIS C AMONG FIREFIGHTERS, PARAMEDICS, EMERGENCY MEDICAL TECHNICIANS AND OTHER EMERGENCY RESPONSE EMPLOYEES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to provide programs to prevent emergency response employees from acquiring Hepatitis C (a viral infection that causes liver inflammation, sometimes leading to serious liver damage).
Seeks to establish a system, training, protocol and scientific research and medical treatment for this virus so that our said personnel will be able to deploy their functions without sacrificing their precious health.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Emergency Response Employees Disease Protection Act”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SY-ALVARADO, JOSE ANTONIO &quot;KUYA JONATHAN&quot; R.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-07-24</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2018-08-01</td></tr></table>